  Subject: Neron-Severi Group NS(J_0(143)) and Hodge/Tate Closure

  The Neron-Severi group NS(A) of an abelian variety A/Q is
  the group of divisor classes modulo algebraic equivalence.
  For J_0(143), NS encodes the algebraic cycle structure that
  underlies both the Hodge conjecture and the Tate conjecture.

  Causal chain:
    M6 -> M8 -> M21 -> M22 -> M23 (BSD) -> NS Tower
    M8C (Zoe-M* bridge: Z=15, M*=4/55) feeds NS rank bound

