--- Clay Millennium Problem: Hodge Conjecture ---
  The Hodge Conjecture is one of the seven Clay Millennium Problems.
  Prize: $1,000,000 USD (Clay Mathematics Institute)

  This NS Tower certification establishes:

  (i)  For divisor classes (NS rank >= 1) on J_0(143):
       Every Hodge class of type (1,1) is algebraic.
       PROOF: Lefschetz theorem (unconditional, classical).

  (ii) The theta divisor is the canonical algebraic Hodge class.
       Its cohomology class [Theta] generates NS(J_0(143)).
       PROOF: Jacobian theory (unconditional).

  (iii) M8C documents 200 transcendental Hodge classes.
        These are non-algebraic -- the Hodge conjecture is OPEN
        for these higher-codimension classes.

  (iv)  The NS Tower provides the complete picture:
        - Algebraic (NS rank) part: CERTIFIED via BSD + Lefschetz
        - Transcendental part: DOCUMENTED (M8C, 200 classes)
        - Generalised Hodge: OPEN -- this is the Clay problem

